Eagleville is a small suburban town located within 30 miles of Pennsylvaniaâ€™s largest city of Philadelphia. It is located in Montgomery County. This town consists of about 10 streets and a population not exceeding 200. The center of town is an elementary school appropriately named Eagleville Elementary, which is part of the Methacton School District. Within the town is one small shopping center consisting of a grocery store, K-mart, a post office, hair cuttery, a pizza place, and a few other assorted stores. There are two parks located in Eagleville; Eskie Park and Eagleville Park. Within the same grounds as Eagleville Park is the Lower Providence public library and the Lower Providence police station.
